    "The SS3T method needs to be used only inside the tumor hence only discarding multiple diffusion shells in the lesion area.",
    "Further research should try to assess whether independently running SS3T with each shell can be combined or not.",
    "On the other hand, Anatomically Constrained Tractography (ACT) has been shown to increase the correspondence between generated streamlines and real fiber bundles, but its usage is not suited for tumoral regions.",
